Hello. We’re Virgin Australia. We’re the airline that’s always done things a
little different. Our way. The Virgin way. We’re on a mission to make flying
better than ‘nice’. And to do that, it takes a team of talented people who are
passionate about customer experience, doing the right thing always, with a
focus on safety – in the air, on the ground and in our workplaces. A team who
values real diversity and inclusion, in a big brand with big ambitions.

##  What you’ll be doing

The objective of the Test Manager role is to act as a source of expertise and
leadership on testing for IT. They will be an advocate of testing, have a
thorough understanding of the importance of testing and will be responsible
for advising on best practise to small projects and / or to stream within
larger projects and programs. The role will also coach junior test analysts if
present in a given project, as well as to lead small teams of testers to
complete a given test phase of a project.

  * Plan and execute all testing phases including, System Test, System Integration Test and User Acceptance Test. 
  * Create test artefacts including Test Strategy, Test Plan and Test cases. 
  * Execute manual and automated test scripts. 
  * Identify and track test defects and execute defect managment. 
  * Maintain governance across all delivery components for audit traceability. 
  * Provide timely and relevant metrics-based reporting on the testing process. 
  * Collaborate with build teams to esnrue timely delivery of code releases and accurate close out of defects. 
  * Manage all resources working within the team, including contractors and vendors. 
  * Provide support to other project teams including data migration, integration and solution architecture in relation to their testing activities (where required). 

##  You’ll be great for this role if you have...

  * Bachelors degree in IT or Computer Science (or equivalent background) 
  * ISTQB qualification or equivalent 
  * 5+ years of expereince as a Test Manager 
  * Experience with project management tools such as Jira, Confluence, qMetry and DevSecOps 
  * Experience in various delivery methodologies including Waterfall and Agile 

##  Desirable but not essential...

  * Masters degree in IT or Computer Science. 
  * Experiance working with cloud platforms such as AWS. 
  * Experience with Java, C++ or C Coding. 
  * Previous airline industry experience. 

##  What you’ll get from us

We’re committed to looking after you, with some of the best benefits and
conditions in the industry – including (but not limited to):

  * Discounted flights for you and your loved ones (including $1000 worth of travel credits per year) 
  * A flexible, hybrid work style. Work from home or the office, adapt your location to suit your style and needs 
  * One of Brisbane’s most admired head office locations, with South Bank train station, a supermarket, pharmacy, and lunch options downstairs plus a 5-minute walk to the Busway, a rooftop restaurant and onsite gym (with a low membership fee) and South Bank Parklands just across the road 
  * Discounts on travel insurance, lounge membership, car hire, accommodation, and experiences worldwide 
  * Cheaper hospitality, retail, technology, beauty and wellness services 
  * Free counselling and access to a wellbeing app to support your physical, mental, social and financial health 
  * ‘Dress for Your Day’ – enjoy the freedom to wear whatever makes you feel great for the type of work you do and the day you have ahead of you. 

